sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.3
    participant API as vLLM OpenAI API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Runner as HPUModelRunner
    participant HPU as Intel Gaudi HPU<br/>(Gaudi2/Gaudi3)
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>(S3/PVC/NFS)
    participant Ray as Ray Head Node<br/>6379/TCP
    participant Peer as HPUWorker Peers<br/>(rank 1..N)
    participant HCCL as HCCL Peer HPUs<br/>RDMA/TCP

    Note over Client,HPU: Flow 1: Model Inference Request
    Client->>Proxy: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Proxy->>Proxy: Validate token against<br/>Kubernetes API
    Proxy->>API: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8000 (localhost, pre-authenticated)
    API->>Runner: Schedule inference
    Runner->>HPU: Forward pass<br/>(in-process, graph execution)
    HPU-->>Runner: Token output
    Runner-->>API: Generation result
    API-->>Proxy: JSON response
    Proxy-->>Client: HTTPS response<br/>TLS 1.3

    Note over Runner,HCCL: Flow 2: Distributed Multi-HPU Inference
    Runner->>Ray: Register worker (rank 0)<br/>TCP/6379
    Ray->>Peer: Initialize workers (rank 1..N)<br/>TCP/dynamic
    Runner->>HCCL: All-reduce / All-gather<br/>RDMA/TCP (plaintext)
    Peer->>HCCL: Tensor/Expert/Data parallelism<br/>RDMA/TCP (plaintext)
    Note over Runner,HCCL: NIXL KV transfer for<br/>disaggregated prefill (optional)

    Note over Runner,S3: Flow 3: Model Weight Loading (Startup)
    Runner->>HF: Download model weights & tokenizer<br/>HTTPS/443, HF_TOKEN Bearer
    HF-->>Runner: Model artifacts
    Runner->>S3: Download model weights<br/>HTTPS/443 or filesystem<br/>AWS IAM / SA auth
    S3-->>Runner: Model weights
    Runner->>HPU: Load weights to HPU memory<br/>(in-process)
    Note over Runner,HPU: FP8/INC/GPTQ/AWQ quantization<br/>applied during loading
